Readme for pyXLIGHT

pyXLIGHT is a stripped down version of Mark Drela's XFOIL code. To
compile the code the user must do two things:

Open f2pyit.sh in the root directory and select which compiler you
will be using:

Two have been tested on linux-intel boxes:

    Intel Fortran Compiler 10.1
    Gfortan compiler

Comment out the version you are not using. 

Second, open src/Makefile and comment out the section coorsponding to
the compiler you are not using. Again, select Intel or Gfortran

Note: Both REAL and COMPLEX versions are included. Comment out a
the complex section if you only want the real version.